    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="473"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d473">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/662</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at London</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRP1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 140]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Referring to your despatch No. 249 of January
                        15<note n="1" xml:id="d473fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_314">p. 314</ref>.</note> in
                    regard to the payment of freight and charges incurred in connection with <pb
                        facs="0580" n="322" xml:id="pg_322"/> the release of American cargoes, you
                    are informed that the Department approves your course in this matter.</p>
                <p>In this connection, it may be added that the Department has no data at hand to
                    show what particular claimants have paid freights.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilbur J. Carr</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
